data.title: Not bad
data.text: We had beef tacos.  They were average. Diffentily not anything to write home about, but the did have a large menu and different salsa that you were allowed to get on you own. If you are on a hurry or in need of a drive through this os not a bad option and open late

data.title: I-25 Exit 102 fresh, fast, and good
data.text: Habanero's is a fresh alternative to fast food chains. The veggie ingredients for tacos and burritos fresh and service prompt. Burritos are generous (almost two meals worth) and price is right. I make it a regular lunch or dinner stop and pit stop (clean bathroom) when passing through Pueblo.

data.title: Mexican food fast
data.text: Didn't want to call it fast food. Very friendly staff & clean place to eat. Just walked over from Comfort Inn, got take out, the back to room to relax. My Texcano burrito was very large & with the side order of rice I was very full. Price was very reasonable. I would go back.

data.title: Very Good Menudo
data.text:
Raised in Pueblo, I think I know my Menudo, which is like the Mother's Milk of Mexican Sopes.

I stopped in today for lunch and ordered a bowl, along with some Guac and Chips. Habanero's definitely serves some of the best I've had.  Plenty of tripe and hominy, and the broth was so good that I was tempted to lift the bowl to my mouth when nobody was looking.  The flour tortillas were really good also.

The guac and chips were served nacho style, sprinkled with cheese.  It would have been a nice presentation, except that the guacamole was among the most tasteless that I have ever eaten, anywhere.  This is surprising because avocados are pretty good at this time of year.  I didn't even finish it as most of it went into the trash.

I can't speak much for service as the clerk wasn't especially friendly.  

I would probably return to try some other menu items.

data.title: Not bad...
data.text: Had two beef tacos that were good. Beans and rice were adequate. Service was prompt and friendly. Nothing really to scream about; average Mexican food...

data.title: Good Fast Mexican Comfort Food
data.text: Nice selection of burritos and other Mexican specialties to choose from.  Breakfast options as well. Service pretty quick.  Food very appetizing and tasty.  Salsa bar available to add to your food.  Drinks and desserts also available, Tres Leche cake particularly tasty.  Would definitely revisit for a quick reasonably priced meal. Location easy to find and plenty of parking.
